Dear Abinandan,

Thank you for the QuestPDF POC output. I have reviewed the PR print 
carefully.

*What the print has achieved*

This is the first working SPINRISE transaction print in the project and 
it is a meaningful milestone. The architecture is proven. Company header 
with the Ashok logo, full address, phone, email — correct. Document 
title, all header fields — PR Number, Date, Requester Name, Department, 
Reference — all present and rendering correctly. The three-line item 
grid with Machine No sub-rows, the Previous Purchase Details columns, 
and the three-panel signature footer are all structurally sound. 
*QuestPDF's capability to produce a production-quality transaction print 
is confirmed from this output.
*
This is exactly the kind of concrete progress that the project needs and 
I want to acknowledge it.

*Four specific corrections before this print is complete
*
Against the M01 FSD requirements — specifically Section 12 Rec 17, Rec 
18, and Rec 28 — I have identified four items the print must address.

*First: *ERP login username is missing. The FSD requires two separate 
identity fields on the PR print. The Requester Name field shows AARTHIMA 
L, which is correct — this is the department employee who needs the 
items, sourced from PO_PRH.REQNAME via PR_EMP.ENAME. But the ERP login 
username — the person who actually typed the PR into the system, from 
PO_PRH.userId or createdby — is not shown anywhere on the print. Both 
must appear as separately labelled fields. Add a second label below or 
alongside Requester Name: 'Created By: [ERP login username]'. Source 
field: PO_PRH.userId or createdby from the API response. This is Section 
12 Rec 17.

*Second: *Footer 'Requested By' shows 'spinrise' as hardcoded text. This 
was clearly a test placeholder. It should display the actual Requester 
Name from the data — AARTHIMA L in this case — or alternatively the ERP 
login user. Not the word 'spinrise'. Replace with the dynamic value from 
the API.

Third: Drawing Number and Catalogue Number columns are missing from the 
item grid. FSD Section 12 Rec 28 is explicit: these two columns must 
always appear on the printed PR, unconditionally, without suppression 
logic, regardless of whether data is present. Source fields: 
IN_ITEM.DRAWNO and IN_ITEM.CATLNO from the ksl_Tran_PORequisition SP via 
J-6. Both columns must be added to the grid and populated from the SP 
output.

*Fourth: *Previous Purchase Date sub-column is blank for all three 
lines. Confirm whether LPO_DATE data exists for these items in the test 
data, or whether the SP is not returning this field. If the SP returns 
it, wire it to the column.

*Alignment polish is secondary to these four content corrections. Fix 
content first, alignment after.*


*On the Excel and CSV evaluation*

The QuestPDF PDF output is confirmed feasible. The Excel and CSV 
capability assessment is still pending and that assessment determines 
whether QuestPDF can replace EPPlus entirely or whether we retain both. 
This evaluation must be completed on Wenesday alongside the alignment 
corrections. It is a simpler test — generate a sample Excel file from a 
data set using the tool and verify that cell formatting, column widths, 
and data types render correctly. It does not require all services 
running simultaneously.

*On the RAM upgrade request*

Your request is reasonable and I support it. Running Visual Studio, SQL 
Server, Chrome, PMS server, and Spinnova server concurrently on 8 GB RAM 
is a genuine hardware constraint for .NET development work. 16 GB is the 
correct specification for this workload. The consistent 90% RAM usage 
you have described is a real productivity constraint and a server 
stability risk.

*I will approve the RAM upgrade. Sasi, please action the procurement 
immediately so this does not delay the next sprint of development work. 
Confirm the upgrade date to me once scheduled.
*
Abinandan, I expect the four print corrections, the alignment polish, 
and the Excel/CSV evaluation all completed and sent to me by end of 
Wednesday. The QuestPDF decision will be finalised once the Excel/CSV 
output is verified.

Regards,
T. Mani
cc: PM Saravanan, TL-Dev Sasi (RAM procurement action)

